Cell.Text: I've got my hands full with something. Don't go far. I'll need you soon.
I'm in the middle of something. But don't go far. I'll need you soon.
Good. I can use someone I can trust.
Excellent. I have a couple tasks for you.
Good. I have some things that need doing.
I'm here to help.
Good. I'm spread thin. I could use the help.
I'm here to help.
Got my hands full as usual.
I'm here to help.
There's plenty that needs doing.
First off, we've learned the location of some rebels scouting our positions throughout the hold. Need to take them out.
First off, there's a couple of Imperials skulking about the hold. Need to cut their throats so they can't make their reports.
First off, they've got some rebels holed up in a nearby settlement. Need to clean them out so our boys can move in.
First off, there's a band of Imperials hiding in a nearby village. We're going to flush them out and put them to the sword.
First, we need to limit Stormcloak capacity and send them a not so subtle message by sabotaging a resource they claim to control.
First problem here is a pack of Imperial dogs drooling over resources stolen from the people. A little sabotage will sour the taste of that victory.
First, we have information regarding the movements of a rebel courier. We need to intercept him and confiscate his package.
First, we've learnt the whereabouts of an Imperial cur fetching documents for his master in Solitude. We need to put a muzzle on that, don't we?
First of all, one of our men was captured by rebels who refuse to surrender him. So we're going to break him out.
First of all, a son of Skyrim rots in an Imperial prison. We'll be getting him out of there soon.
First of all, I need to sew confusion and doubt through the rebel troops. I want to assassinate their commanding officer.
First, if we can assassinate their commander, we'll be able to strike them while they're busy tucking their tails between their legs.
First, our intelligence suggests one of the rebel garrisons has become disaffected. If we play our cards right, we should be able to turn them.
First off, we hear a group of Imperial legionnaires are coming around to our way of thinking. With a little encouragement they'll join our side.
First off, seems the Jarl's Steward might be vulnerable to blackmail. Need to investigate that possibility.
First off, it seems that we might be able to blackmail the Jarl's Steward. I need to find out for sure.
First on my list, is a problem with our supply caravans being constantly harassed by a giant. Need to deal with that hairy brute. And soon.
The last few supply caravans have been attacked... by a giant. As if I didn't have enough to deal with. Need that damn hairy brute straightened out.
First, I need to get a handle on rebel operations. Need to discretely liberate some documents from their headquarters.
First, I need to know what the Imperials are planning. Need to slip into their headquarters, grab plans, maps, something useful like that.
First of all, I'd like to drum up some more support from the local populace. I have someone in mind.
First of all, there's someone in particular I'd like to win over to our cause.
First off, there's an Orc hanging around causing me headaches. Something about a vision quest he needs help with.
First off, there's a damn Orc hanging around getting in the way. He's been yammering on about needing help with some kind of vision quest.
First, we're mounting an attack on the Fort. We aim to confiscate it from the rebels.
First, we're attacking the fort. I want that fort.
[S] Secondly, some rebel scouts that have seen too much are moving through the hold. Need to take them out before they report back to their leaders.
[S] Secondly, we got a couple of Imperial spies roaming through the hold. Need to put an end to that.
[S] Secondly, we got more of 'em hiding in a village, using the local populace as shields. Not to worry. We can dispatch them without harming the locals.
[S] Secondly, we plan on liberating a settlement from Imperial hands.
[S] Secondly, I need to cripple rebel production capabilities with a little sabotage.
[S] Next problem - Imperial thieves have, yet again, stolen an important resource. So we're gonna take it from them permanently - by destroying it.
[S] Soldiers win wars, but where to put them is the key. We have word of an enemy courier in the area. We aim to confiscate his documents.
[S] And then, it seems an Imperial worm wiggles it's way back home, carrying information stolen from us. We need to steal it back.
[S] And perhaps more importantly, I need to break one of our boys out of a rebel controlled fort.
[S] And perhaps more importantly, we have a brother rotting in an Imperial prison. He won't languish in there long, will he now?
[S] And we have an opportunity to slay the rebel field commander. Without a clear command structure, they should fall into confusion and disarray.
[S] We also have the opportunity to slay an Imperial Legate. That'll put fear and confusion into those faithless dogs.
[S] And we understand a rebel garrison is close to abandoning the resistance. We need to send them a little encouragement.
[S] And we hear a handful of Imperials are realizing they are Stormcloaks at heart. We need to send them a little encouragement.
[S] Next, I need a little investigating to confirm the possibility of blackmailing the Jarl's Steward.
[S] Next, I need dirt on the Jarl's Steward. Heard there's blackmail potential there.
[S] And then there's a tiny problem with a giant that's been raiding our supply caravans... You heard me right. A giant. Need to put a stop to that.
[S] And then there's a tiny problem with a giant attacking our supply caravans. A giant! As if I didn't have enough to deal with.
[S] I also would like to get a handle on what the rebels are planning - slip into their headquarters and steal their war plans.
[S] Also, I need a peek inside Imperial headquarters, ideally lifting some documents detailing their plans. I need to know what to concentrate on.
[S] Then there's a little matter of some recruiting. I have someone in mind I'd like to join our campaign.
[S] I need to send someone out to do a little recruiting. There's someone in particular I'd like to join us.
[S] And then there's this Orc who's been hanging around causing me headaches. Something about a vision quest he needs help with.
[S] And as if that wasn't enough. I got this damn Orc hanging around, getting in the way, yapping about needing help with some kind of vision quest.
[S] Secondly, we're mounting an attack on the Fort. I want to gain a fortified position here before we launch our final attack on the capital.
[S] Secondly, I want to take the fort here. Having a fortified position will make it easier for us to amass men for our ultimate attack on the capital.
[S] I'm disappointed in your failure. But the Empire still needs you. I'll have to over look it for now.
[S] Turns out you're a screw up like the rest. But I still need you. So I'll overlook it for now.
[S] Excellent. I can move more soldiers through the area now that I know those scouts are dead.
[S] Good job! With those Imperial scouts out of the way, I can be more aggressive about where I send our men.
[S] <<Shared>> You gave those mongrels a real whipping, eh? Good work. We'll be sure to send a garrison to reinforce the area and keep the peace.
[S] <<Shared>> Excellent! We've hit 'em where it hurts. Repairs will be needed when we take over, but at least the Stormcloaks won't benefit in the meantime.
[S] <<Shared>> We hit 'em where it hurts. As soon as we can, we'll take over - make the needed repairs. In the meantime, the people no longer slave for the Empire.
[S] <<Shared>> You made it! I'm impressed. It was a gamble, but turned out well.
[S] <<Shared>> You're alive! It was a gamble - but as Talos keeps us, we keep each other - I wasn't going to just let them rot in there.
[S] Good. They'll think twice before crossing us while their command structure is in disarray.
[S] I pray Talos overlooks our less than honorable approach. But he knows our purpose is just and true. I'm glad you made it out alive.
[S] Good work. This was a double victory. We took a garrison away from the Stormcloaks and further proved the hollowness of their cause.
[S] Excellent. That's one less settlement in Imperial hands, and one more sign to all that our cause is true.
[S] Good work. I'll send some men with a wagon to collect the prize. We can use the weapons here, and I'll pass on the coin to Solitude.
[S] Well done! I'll send men with a wagon to collect our prize. We'll put the weapons to use here, and I'll send the coin back to Windhelm.
[S] Good job. The more citizens that join the fight against the rebels, the sooner they will see the futility of their rebellion.
[S] We grow that much stronger with each son and daughter of Skyrim who joins us. Down with the Emperor!
[S] Thanks for taking care of that. I don't think that will be the last we see of that Orc. It's always good to gain allies.
[S] Thanks for dealing with that orc. Something tells me that's not the last time we'll see him. And, something tells me that might not be a bad thing.
[S] Good job! I knew I gave the mission to the right person.
[S] Good job! Ulfric was right about you. I'm glad to have you with us!
G|Speak with Ulfric, he's expecting word from Whiterun.

[S] G|We're taking the city. Meet the soldiers gathering for the attack. Move it!
[S] G|We're attacking Riften. Meet the soldiers gathering for the attack. Move it!
[S] G|We're mounting our final attack on Windhelm. You're needed on the front line. Get a move on soldier!
[S] G|We're taking the capital. Meet the soldiers gathering for the attack. Move it!
[S] G|We're taking Dawnstar. Get down there and join the rest of the men gathering for the attack. Now soldier!
[S] G|We're taking Winterhold. Get over there and join the rest of the men gathering for the attack. Now soldier!
[S] G|The Stormcloaks are here. In force. Get down to the front line. This is it. We must hold the city. Move it!
How can I help?
G|We're ready to launch our attack on Solitude. But the Emperor's cousin is getting married! We can't risk attacking now. So we'll bide our time.
How can I help?
G|We're ready to launch our attack on Solitude. But the Emperor's visiting! We can't risk attacking now. So we'll bide our time.
How can I help?
[S] G|We're taking the city. Meet the brothers gathering for the attack. Fight well or die well. Talos be with you.
How can I help?
[S] G|We're taking Whiterun. Meet the brothers gathering for the attack. Fight well or die well. Talos be with you.
How can I help?
[S] G|We're mounting our attack on Markarth. Get over there and join the brothers gathering for the attack. This is it now! Talos be with you.
How can I help?
[S] G|We're mounting our final attack on Solitude. Get over there and join the rest of the army. They'll be launching the attack soon. Talos be with you!
[S] G|We're taking the capital. Meet the brothers gathering for the attack. Fight well or die well. Talos be with you.
[S] G|We're taking Falkreath. Get over there with the others. Fight well or die well.
[S] G|We're liberating Morthal. Join the brothers gathering for the attack. Talos be with you.
How can I help?
[S] G|The Imperials are here. All lined up pretty-like in their shiny armor. We'll put a few dents in those bastards before we give up the city. Move it!
